    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Best Friend? Maybe Not</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steven D Price letter on Jane E Brody December 26 Personal Health column about falls warns that pets like dogs and cats can get in way of older people and cause them to fall</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Taking Steps So Aging Does Not Mean Falling'' (Dec. 26): Pets, both those owned by seniors and by other people, should be added to the list of potential hazards cited in Jane Brody's column about seniors falling.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Taking Steps So Aging Does Not Mean Falling'' (Dec. 26): Pets, both those owned by seniors and by other people, should be added to the list of potential hazards cited in Jane Brody's column about seniors falling.</p>
        <p>Cats and small dogs have a way of getting underfoot, often when least expected, while large dogs that jump up to greet older people can knock them over.</p>
        <p>Steven D. Price  New York</p>
      </block>
